  "response": "If Mark Zuckerberg were to build Facebook today, here's a recommended technology stack with rationale:\n\nFrontend:\n- React.js (with TypeScript)\n  - Declarative, component-based architecture\n  - High performance\n  - Strong ecosystem\n  - Facebook actually created React, so perfect fit\n  - Easy to scale and maintain\n\nBackend:\n- Go (Golang)\n  - Highly concurrent\n  - Built-in concurrency support\n  - Excellent performance\n  - Easy scalability\n  - Strong typing\n  - Used by companies like Google, Uber\n\nDatabase:\n- Cassandra (NoSQL)\n  - Horizontal scalability\n  - High write throughput\n  - Distributed architecture\n  - Used by Facebook originally\n  - Great for social graph data\n\nCaching:\n- Redis\n  - Ultra-fast in-memory storage\n  - Complex data structures\n  - Pub/Sub messaging\n  - Low latency\n\nInfrastructure:\n- Kubernetes\n- Docker\n- Cloud-agnostic deployment\n- Microservices architecture\n\nReal-time Communication:\n- WebSockets\n- gRPC\n- GraphQL\n\nAdditional Technologies:\n- Machine Learning: TensorFlow\n- Big Data: Apache Spark\n- Monitoring: Prometheus\n\nThis stack prioritizes scalability, performance, and modern development practices.",
